[[[description]]]
Argument information for built-in functions is important for the sake of the reflection API.

The `ZEND_ARG_TYPE_INFO` macro is used to specify the argument is a build-in type like a boolean, an integer, a string or a resource.

Constant | type
---------- | ----------
_IS_BOOL | bool
IS_LONG | int
IS_DOUBLE | float
IS_STRING | string
IS_ARRAY | array
IS_OBJECT | object
IS_RESOURCE | resource
IS_CALLABLE | callable
IS_ITERABLE | iterable

[[[additional_information]]]
### Example

    ZEND_BEGIN_ARG_WITH_RETURN_TYPE_INFO_EX(arginfo_date, 0, 1, IS_STRING, 0)
        ZEND_ARG_TYPE_INFO(0, format, IS_STRING, 0)
        ZEND_ARG_TYPE_INFO(0, timestamp, IS_LONG, 0)
    ZEND_END_ARG_INFO()
